{"id": 7649, "title": "Ticket #7649: Limit number of threads for R jobs", "description": "<blockquote>\nI was investigating why BaTLab builds were running slowly in CHTC. It turns out that many R processes were overloading the system. It turns out that R looks at OMP_THREAD_LIMIT to limit cores and we do not set that environment variable. So, let's add it.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-May-21 09:01</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/9eab91a5b112d3283abb7546ce7a0da6195b71dc\">[59700]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7649\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7649'); return false;\" title=\"Limit number of threads for R jobs\">#7649</a></span>) Add OMP_THREAD_LIMIT to list of env vars that starter sets  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2020-May-21 09:34", "status": "resolved", "created": "2020-May-21 08:45", "fixed_version": "2020-May-21 08:45", "broken_version": "", "priority": "2", "subsystem": "DaemonsExecNode", "assigned_to": "tim", "derived_from": "", "creator": "tim", "rust": "", "customer_group": "chtc", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}